<HEADLINE>
Jurors in Blake murder case resume deliberations after reviewing testimony
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
LOS ANGELES
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jurors in the murder case against actor Robert Blake began their fifth day of
deliberations Thursday after spending more than an hour at the end of the
previous day reviewing testimony in the trial.
</P>
<P>
The panel Wednesday went over statements by three people at the restaurant where
the actor and his wife, 44-year-old Bonny Lee Bakley, had dinner before she was
shot and killed in May 2001. It was the first time jurors have made a request to
review testimony.
</P>
<P>
The 71-year-old star of TV's "Baretta" and the movie "In Cold Blood" is charged
with murder in the death of his wife, along with two counts of solicitation of
murder and a special circumstance of lying in wait. If convicted, he could be
sentenced to life in prison.
</P>
